ref:_00D7091pB._500Q000CIgZl:ref

Thank you. I was able to get past the error and got the report, but the report is blank, saying there are no stale files, which I know that is not correct.

I'm guessing I have some setting misconfigured. Below are my current settings for the FS_CleanupAssessment job. Can you tell if anything needs to be changed or know why I'm not seeing any stale files in the reports?

Number of days after which a resource's LastModified timestamp classifies it as stale - Set to 365
If 1, LastModified will be used to calculate staleness. If 0, LastAccessed will be used - Set to 1
UNC Paths of folders to exclude from staleness consideration (recursive) - None
Lower bound for files to be included in the FileDetails table (by LastModified, in days) - Set to 365
Upper bound for files to be included in the FileDetails table (by LastModified, in days) - Set to 7300



Brandon Flaming

I.T. Department

Amvac Chemical Corp.

(949) 260-6041
